**59. If the price of oil increases by 25%, by what percentage should consumption be reduced so that total expenditure remains unchanged? [36th BCS]**<br>
a. 16%<br> b. `20%`<br> c. 25%<br> d. 24%

+++ check

Given price increase = (25%)

Required reduction formula:
$$
\left(\frac{x}{100+x}\times100\right)\%
$$

Substituting (x = 25):

$$
\frac{25}{100+25}\times100 = \frac{25}{125}\times100 = 20\%
$$

**Answer: 20%**
+++

