**62. If the price of cloth decreases by 20%, by what percentage can a person increase consumption without increasing expenditure? [Passport &amp; Immigration Assistant Director - 2014; ACC Inspector - 1998]**<br>
a. `25%`<br> b. 20%<br> c. 33⅓%<br> d. 40%

+++ check

Given price decrease = (20%)

Required increase:
$$
\left(\frac{20}{100-20}\times100\right)\%
= \frac{20}{80}\times100
= 25\%
$$

**Answer: 25%**
+++

